the Middle East,
now on an assignment that is his
lifetime.

14:34.474 --> 14:38.511 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
With support from the National
Geographic
Society, the Nieman and Knight
Foundations

14:38.544 --> 14:42.281 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and others, he has walked across
deserts and
mountains.

14:42.315 --> 14:44.083 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
So, why do this?

14:44.117 --> 14:51.390 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAUL SALOPEK: There has got to
be a space
to slow down, analyze and absorb
more meaningful

14:51.424 --> 14:55.361 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
information. I don't think we
