15:14.580 --> 15:18.985 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
walking between stories shows me
connections
that didn't -- I didn't used to
see when I

15:19.018 --> 15:20.486 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
would parachute in.

15:20.520 --> 15:22.455 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: And what are
we saying?
What is humanity telling you?

15:22.488 --> 15:26.492 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAUL SALOPEK: The same stories
over and over
again. It's the same classic
stories of complaint,

15:26.526 --> 15:34.167 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of joy, of aspiration, of hope,
of hopes dashed.
And I never get tired of them.

15:34.200 --> 15:37.703 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: We caught up
with him in
Southern Georgia's Caucasus
Mountains, near

15:37.737 --> 15:43.376 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Armenia, where the walk was
stopped late last
fall at this destroyed
Soviet-era building.

15:43.409 --> 15:48.047 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAUL SALOPEK: Last November, we
